<SupportPage
  locale="en"
  path="/support/shipping-delivery.html"
  title="Shipping & Delivery | GYUTRON Support"
  description="How GYUTRON ships industrial hardware worldwide from Hong Kong and Shenzhen — order processing, lead times, incoterms, customs and duties, packaging, tracking and delivery inspection."
  eyebrow="Help & Support"
  heading="Shipping & Delivery"
  crumb="Shipping & Delivery"
  intro="We ship industrial hardware to manufacturers and integrators worldwide from our Hong Kong and Shenzhen operations."
>
  <p class="support-lead">Shipping terms for any order are confirmed in your quotation or order confirmation. The summary below describes how we typically handle delivery for B2B orders.</p>

  <h2>Order processing</h2>
  <p>Orders are processed from our facilities in Hong Kong and Shenzhen, Guangdong. Once an order is confirmed and payment terms are met, in-stock items are prepared for dispatch promptly; configured or made-to-order items are scheduled according to the agreed lead time.</p>

  <h2>Lead times</h2>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>In-stock products</strong> — typically dispatched within a few business days of order confirmation.</li>
    <li><strong>Configured / made-to-order products</strong> — lead time depends on options and quantity and is confirmed on the quotation.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Incoterms &amp; carriers</h2>
  <p>International shipments are arranged under agreed Incoterms (for example EXW, FOB or DAP) using established couriers and freight forwarders. For larger or palletized orders we can coordinate with your nominated forwarder.</p>

  <h2>Customs, duties &amp; taxes</h2>
  <p>For cross-border shipments, import duties, taxes and customs clearance are the responsibility of the importer of record unless otherwise agreed. We provide the commercial documentation required for clearance.</p>

  <h2>Packaging</h2>
  <p>Products are protected with industrial packaging appropriate to the device, including ESD protection for sensitive electronics. Multi-line orders may ship in multiple parcels.</p>

  <h2>Tracking &amp; delivery</h2>
  <ul>
    <li>Tracking details are provided once your order is dispatched.</li>
    <li>Partial shipments may be made for multi-line orders to avoid holding the entire order for one item.</li>
    <li>Please inspect goods on receipt and report any transit damage or discrepancy promptly so we can assist with the carrier claim.</li>
  </ul>

  <div class="support-note">Delivery addresses, Incoterms and lead times are confirmed during order review. For a delivery estimate to your location, please <a href="/contact-sales.html">contact our sales team</a>.</div>
</SupportPage>
